  "text": "Financial satisfaction is closely connected to financial capacity, which has been described as the ability to effectively manage economic resources to attain wellbeing [CITATION_1] . To measure financial capacity, we used the variables Personality 1-3 (adequate monthly income, access to the purchase of cheap products, reserve for unexpected expenditure) which were constructed on the basis of questions used in research by Taylor [CITATION_2] .",
